IT Budget




Ocwen Financial Corporation iprovides loan servicing, mortgage fulfillment, asset management, receivables management, and other services. It operates in two segments : Ocwen Asset Management and Ocwen Solutions. It also offers technology products, such as the REAL suite of applications used… MoreOcwen Financial Corporation iprovides loan servicing, mortgage fulfillment, asset management, receivables management, and other services. It operates in two segments : Ocwen Asset Management and Ocwen Solutions. It also offers technology products, such as the REAL suite of applications used in loan origination and loan servicing.
At Ocwen Financial Corporation, there is some overlap between corporate IT groups and customer-facing technology groups in support of the company's REALsuite product. The VP of Business Intelligence and Data Management oversees reporting, data warehousing, analytics and architecture, providing IT… MoreAt Ocwen Financial Corporation, there is some overlap between corporate IT groups and customer-facing technology groups in support of the company's REALsuite product. The VP of Business Intelligence and Data Management oversees reporting, data warehousing, analytics and architecture, providing IT strategy. The Network Administration group specializes in network security, while also covering data storage and telecommunications. The Business Analysis and MIS Reporting groups work together in support of applications and databases. The IT Financial Systems group is responsible for the support of financial applications and systems used across the company.

The company relies primarily on Oracle technologies for business process management.

Ocwen Financial recently acquired Homeward Residential towards the end of 2012. The company is in the process of integrating Homeward Residential and when the initiative is complete, Homeward Residential's operations will be overseen by Ocwen. Ocwen recently acquired Liberty Home Equity Solutions, a former business line for Genworth Financial, and Residential Capital LLC (ResCap) a former business line of Ally Financial. Integration of these two business lines are on hold until they can separate their systems and infrastructure from their respective parent companies.





